Norma Jean &amp; Marilyn is a 1996 made-for-TV biographical film produced by Home Box Office and premiered on 18 May 1996.
It was partially-based on "Norma Jean: My Secret Life With Marilyn Monroe" by actor Ted Jordan (played by Josh Charles), who claimed to have had a years-long relationship with Monroe.
Norma Jean was her reality." In dream-like scenes, Monroe and her former self appear together, with Norma Jean sometimes taunting Marilyn.
